        "title": "은/는 (topic particle)",
        "content": [
            {
                "title": "Appending 은/는 to a noun denotes the topic of the sentence.",
                "details": "When the noun ends in a consonant, the ending 은 is used. When the noun ends in a vowel, 는 is used. The topic particle is used to specify which thing you are talking about, in contrast to other things. The English equivalent might be the use of The [noun] to indicate a specific noun."
